            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-15T17:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="230" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d230">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">C.P.(Gen)Doc.1.Q.4.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Article 4</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-10-15T23:59:59+01:00" notBefore="1946-07-29T00:00:00+01:00">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>In Article 4, paragraph 1, a new second paragraph is to be added as follows:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Hungary also binds herself to dissolve all organisations existing on her
                            territory whose aim is to disseminate revisionism openly or secretly,
                            and to prohibit in future the existence and activity of such
                            organisations as aim at spreading revisionism or exciting a hostile
                            attitude to Czechoslovakia among Hungarians.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">Argument</hi>.</p>
                <p>Czechoslovakia also considers it necessary to forbid not only hostile propaganda
                    by Hungary but every other activity tending to threaten the security of other
                    states. It is equally essential to prohibit not only fascist propaganda but also
                    its correlative “revisionism”, which would continue to be aimed against and to
                    threaten Czechoslovakia.</p>
            </div>
